4hl.title: Index two subgroup of group is normal
4hl.clickbait: An easy (though not very widely applicable) criterion for a subgroup to be normal.
4hl.text:
Let $H$ be a [-subgroup] of the [-3gd] $G$, of [index_of_subgroup index] $2$.
Then $H$ is a [-4h6] of $G$.

# Proof

We must show that $H$ is closed under [4gk conjugation] by elements of $G$.

Since $H$ has index $2$ in $G$, there are two left [group_coset cosets]: $H$ and $xH$ for some specific $x$.
There are also two right cosets: $H$ and $Hy$.

Now, since $x \not \in H$, it must be the case that $x \in Hy$; so without loss of generality, $x = y$.

Hence $xH = Hx$ and so $xHx^{-1} = H$.

It remains to show that $H$ is closed under conjugation by *every* element of $G$.
But every element of $G$ is either in $H$, or in $xH$; so it is either $h$ or $xh$, for some $h \in H$.

- $hHh^{-1}$ is equal to $H$ since $hH = H$ and $Hh^{-1} = H$.
- $xh H (xh)^{-1} = xhHh^{-1} x^{-1} = xHx^{-1} = H$.

This completes the proof.
